issues.description: The problem statement / UML specifies ExcellenceLand.excellentEnough as a boolean, but the solution implements it as a String (field, constructor parameter and getter). This type mismatch will confuse students about the intended type and cause tests that expect a boolean to fail.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the type of ExcellenceLand.excellentEnough in the solution (and any template placeholders) from String to boolean. Update the constructor parameter type and the getter return type accordingly (e.g. private boolean excellentEnough; public ExcellenceLand(double excellencyLevel, boolean excellentEnough, List<Ride> rides) { ... } public boolean getExcellentEnough() { ... }). This will align the implementation with the UML/problem statement and expected tests.
